\section{Q4}
Show that any language $A$ is Turing-recognizable (CE) iff $A \leq _m A_{TM}$ (i.e.
$A$ is mapping reducible to $A_{TM}$). \newline
\indent \textbf{Sol:}
$(\Rightarrow)$ If $A$ is recognizable, there exists a TM $M_A$ that recognizes it. Define the reduction $f(w) = \langle M_A, w \rangle$. Then $w \in A \iff \langle M_A, w \rangle \in A_{TM}$. Since $f$ is computable, $A \leq_m A_{TM}$. \newline
$(\Leftarrow)$ If $A \leq_m A_{TM}$, there exists a computable function $f$ such that $w \in A \iff f(w) \in A_{TM}$. To recognize $A$, on input $w$, compute $f(w)$ and simulate the universal TM on $f(w)$. If it accepts, \textbf{accept}.

