\section{Q5}
Show that any language A is decidable (computable) iff $A \leq_m 0^*1^*$. \newline
\indent \textbf{Sol: }
$(\Rightarrow)$ If $A$ is decidable, let $M_D$ be its decider. Define $f(w)$: Run $M_D$ on $w$. If it accepts, output $01$. If it rejects, output $10$. Since $01 \in 0^*1^*$ and $10 \notin 0^*1^*$, and $M_D$ always halts, $f$ is a valid reduction. \newline
$(\Leftarrow)$ If $A \leq_m 0^*1^*$, there is a computable $f$ such that $w \in A \iff f(w) \in 0^*1^*$. Since $0^*1^*$ is a regular language, it is decidable. To decide $A$, compute $f(w)$ and check if it belongs to $0^*1^*$.

